\chapter{mentipy}
\label{mentipy}

\texttt{mentipy} is a self-hosted classroom polling system built around one
simple invariant: a question's content determines its identity.  That identity
is then reused by the slide generator, the HTTP server, and the results viewer.

\section{Package facade}

The implementation lives in smaller modules, but user code should not need to
remember where each public helper resides.  The package root therefore re-exports
the small surface we expect PythonTeX users and CLI users to care about.

