The version constant keeps the generated package self-describing, while
[[__all__]] documents the intended public API explicitly.

<<constants>>=
__version__ = "0.1"

__all__ = [
    "MCQuestion",
    "OpenQuestion",
    "Question",
    "ScaleQuestion",
    "Store",
    "mc",
    "open_text",
    "question",
    "question_from_dict",
    "question_hash",
    "scale",
    "serve",
    "__version__",
]
@

There is no runtime logic here beyond the re-exports, so the generated package
body is intentionally empty apart from the constants above.

